President Donald J. Trump has proclaimed March 21, 2017, as National Agriculture Day in the United States. In his proclamation, he highlights the important role that farmers and ranchers play in feeding the world, fueling the nation's economy, and leading global markets in output and productivity. He emphasizes the efficiency and innovation of American agriculture, which has provided abundance and jobs across the country. President Trump acknowledges the sector's contribution to the nation's net trade balance, generating 10 percent of exports and millions of American jobs. He also recognizes the importance of a safe and plentiful domestic food supply for national security and the need to safeguard the sustainable resource base for future generations. The president encourages all Americans to observe National Agriculture Day and express their appreciation for farmers and ranchers.